item.title: Industrialcraft Mod Spotlight - (Technic Pack Part 2)
item.description:
Industrialcraft Mod Spotlight - (Technic Pack Part 2)
Please donate to the makers of your favourite mods and encourage them not to use adf.ly in the donation comments! These mods are particularly awesome, so please support their makers! Lewis backdates his Minecraft to 1.7.3 and looks at a combination of awesome industry-style mods compiled by an awesome fellow named Kakermix as the "Technic pack". I have shied away from this for a while because it's so complicated, but once I got stuck in, I realised it was totally and utterly awesome. The Technic combination mod pack is out-of-date and completely unofficial, so use it at your own risk! You should be able to find a way to downgrade your version of minecraft back to 1.7.3 with this mod: http://www.minecraftforum.net/topic/106402-tool-cyborgs-tools-mcnostalgia-103/ The Technic pack is item.title: Disney AppMATes: The New Mobile Application Toys for iPad
item.description:
Disney AppMATes: The New Mobile Application Toys for iPad
Introducing Disney AppMATes - a new line of toys that comes to life digitally when used with an Apple iPad allowing kids to use the tablet's screen as a virtual play mat. The Appmates toy line features miniature Disney•Pixar Cars 2 vehicles with sensors on the base of each toy that are recognized as a unique footprint by an app with no cable or Bluetooth connection required. Simply download the free Cars 2 Appmates app from the iTunes app store, place your favorite Appmates toy character on the screen and play. Ages 4+ Toys available Oct. 1 at national retailers, Apple Store, Apple Store online, Disney Store and www.DisneyStore.com with vehicle two-packs featuring four characters including Lightning McQueen, Tow Mater, Finn McMissile, and Holley Shiftwell. Two additional characters -- Francesco Bernoulli and Shu Todoroki -- will launch in November and be available exclusively through Apple Store and Apple Store online.
